author: Justin Hawkins Rides Again
description:
Today I'm paying tribute to Terry Reid who has died, aged 75. He was responsible for one of my favourite albums, "Seed of Memory" and had, in my opinion,  the greatest voice. The second part of this tribute is a review of "Faith To Arise" from that album. 
Terry contributed so much to music. Many of the headlines this week mention Led Zeppelin - claiming that Terry "turned down" a request to join the band. The reality was more nuanced and it was actually Terry who introduced Robert Plant and John Bonham to Jimmy Page. Anyway, there is a lot more to say, but I urge you to listen to his music.
